headline: Uber rival Bolt's annual revenue hits 2 billion euros
summary: The company said in a statement its app has reached over 50 countries and is the No. 1 operator in more than 20 of them, having widened its offering to ride-hailing, scooter and e-bike rental, food and grocery delivery and car sharing.  Its home country of Estonia is one of Europe's largest tech hubs, housing over 1,450  startups according to the government.  "I don't really agree that you cannot figure out how to do world class marketing or engineering from Europe," Bolt's Chief Executive Markus Villig said in the statement.
